https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites
Can TG4 access your information which is held by the third-party social media platforms where you get the TG4 App e.g. Facebook and when you access the players?
We may collect personal data that is already associated with your third-party social media platform account, such as your name and your email address.
You may also have the option of sharing additional information with TG4 through your third-party social media platform account.  If you choose to provide such personal data, during or after registration, you are giving TG4 permission to use, share, and store it in accordance with this Privacy Statement.
What personal information does TG4 collect when you access the players?
When you access the players we may ask you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information that can be used to contact or identify you. Personally identifiable information may include, but is not limited to:
Name
Email address
Password
County
Standard of Irish
Age
Gender
How will TG4 use your information obtained through your use of the players and our social media sites?
TG4 may use this personal information for the following purposes:
Usage: To monitor your usage.
Contact: To contact you by email, telephone calls, SMS, or other forms of electronic communication, such as a mobile application’s push notifications regarding updates or informative communications related to the functionalities, products or contracted services, including security updates.
Manage requests: To manage your requests to us.
Performance of a contract: For the performance of a contract in relation to items you buy through our players.
Access to functionalities: The personal data you provide can give you access to different functionalities of the players that are available to you as a registered user.
For other purposes: We may use your information for other purposes, such as data analysis, identifying usage trends, determining the effectiveness of our promotional campaigns and to evaluate and improve the players, products, services, marketing and your experience.
Does TG4  pass any personal information to third parties?
It is not TG4 policy to pass on personal information to any third parties. When you purchase from the TG4 Shop or on TG4 online services we will have details of your account but we will not have details of your payment method. The order is processed by a service provider who is contracted to TG4.  The privacy policy of the relevant service provider will apply and links to these privacy policies are set out immediately below.
The service provider is under a contractual obligation to keep personal information for the purpose for which it is intended and not to pass on any personal information to any third parties.
When a viewer purchases items on the players the privacy policy of the relevant third party social media platform applies to the payment. Links to the Apple and Google privacy policies in relation to payment are below:
Apple Store In-App Payments
Their Privacy Policy can be viewed at
https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/en-ww/
Google Play In-App Payments
Their Privacy Policy can be viewed at
https://www.google.com/policies/privacy/
How do you know your personal information is kept safe and secure if you choose to provide your details for services on the players and on the social media sites?
TG4 servers which hold any personal information are in TG4 HQ in secure locations and on Amazon Web Services secure servers hosted in Ireland. Credit and debit card details are not stored by TG4. If you purchase items in respect of an individual programme those purchases may be through the app store and in that instance the purchase will be governed by the privacy policy of that app store. In addition, if you wish to buy books and dvds which are advertised on our players you are directed to the relevant third party suppliers to purchase the item and the purchase will be governed by the privacy policy of those suppliers. At present the suppliers are as follows but additional suppliers may be added in the future: Cló Iar Chonnachta, Spailpín, Cartoon Saloon, Sea Fever Productions, Bankostales.com, Futa Fata and The Education company of Ireland.
What other Personal Data is collected by TG4?
We collect feedback from you which means information you voluntarily provide to us when you provide feedback including queries, complaints, comments, or when you enter competitions or interact with TG4 in any way. The information is kept for 1  year and it is then anonymised and kept forever.
How will TG4 use your information?
If TG4 acquires any personal information about you through your use of the players or the TG4 social media sites TG4 will ensure that the information will only be used for the purposes for which it is gathered and it will not be distributed or used for any other purpose however it may be used in the additional ways detailed in this Privacy Statement where you have given consent for such additional uses.
Does TG4 currently transfer any of the information collected abroad for other purposes?
TG4 does not transfer any personal information abroad.
What happens if TG4 transfers your personal data abroad at some time in the future?
If in the future TG4 transfers your personal data abroad it means that this information may be transferred to — and maintained on — computers located outside of Ireland. If this type of transfer happens in future TG4 will ensure that no transfer will take place to an organization or a country unless there are adequate controls in place to secure your personal data. TG4 will use European Union approved “standard contractual clauses” to protect your personal data if this happens.
Are the players hosted in Ireland?
Yes, the players are hosted in Ireland.
How long will your information be retained by TG4?
TG4 will ensure that personal information will not be retained for longer than it is required and that once the initial purposes for gathering the information have become irrelevant the information will not be retained.
In addition we will retain and use your personal data to the extent necessary to comply with our legal obligations (for example, if we are required to retain your data to comply with applicable laws), to comply with legal and regulatory obligations, to resolve disputes, to enforce our legal agreements and policies, to protect and defend the rights or property of TG4, to prevent or investigate possible wrongdoing in connection with the  players or TG4 social media sites and  to protect the personal safety of users of the players and TG4 social media sites, or the public and for legitimate business purposes. In those circumstances we may disclose your personal data to the relevant authorities.
Legal Basis for Processing Personal Data under GDPR
We may process your personal data under the following conditions:
Consent:
you have explicitly given your consent for processing personal data for one or more specific purposes under s71 of the Data Protection Act 2018. You may withdraw your consent at any time.
Performance of a contract:
where it is necessary for the performance of an agreement with you.
Performance of a function under legislation
TG4 has the functions set out in s118 of the Broadcasting Act 2009 (as amended) and we process personal data in performing those functions under s38(1) of the Data Protection Act 2018.
Legal advice and legal proceedings:
for the purposes of legal advice and legal proceedings under s41 of the Data Protection Act 2018.
Archiving in the public interest:
for the purposes of archiving in the public interest and for statistical purposes under s42 of the Data Protection Act 2018.
Journalistic purposes:
for journalistic, artistic and literary purposes  under s43 of the Data Protection Act 2018 which facilitates TG4’s right to freedom of expression. Similarly, production companies may use the personal data of contributors who participate in programmes produced for TG4 in accordance with the privacy policy of each individual production company and in reliance on the journalistic purposes ground and contributors should review the privacy policy of the applicable production company.
What is the legal basis for processing the personal data detailed in this Privacy Statement?
Type of processing/purpose:
Analysis of programming and the selection of programming which matches viewers preferences/ Identification of location of viewers – Legal basis: Performance of a function under legislation under the Broadcasting Act 2009 (as amended) which requires TG4 to establish and maintain a broadcasting service, establish websites, establish archives and create and acquire programming.  Additional legal basis: Archiving in the public interest.
Type of processing/purpose:
Data relating to participation in a programme – Legal basis: Performance of a function under legislation under the Broadcasting Act 2009 (as amended) which requires TG4 to establish and maintain a broadcasting service and create programming. Additional legal basis: Performance of a function under legislation under the Broadcasting Act 2009 (as amended) which requires TG4 to establish and maintain archives.  Additional legal basis: Archiving in the public and for statistical purposes under s42 of the Data Protection Act 2018.  Additional legal basis: Journalistic purpose under s43 of the Data Protection Act 2018.
Type of processing/purpose:
sale of advertising, products and services – Legal basis: performance of a contract and performance of a function under legislation under the Broadcasting Act 2009 (as amended) which requires TG4 to exploit commercial opportunities.
Type of processing/purpose:
Competitions/email alerts/newsletters – Legal basis: Performance of a function under legislation under the Broadcasting Act 2009 (as amended) which requires TG4 to establish and maintain a broadcasting service.  Additional legal basis: consent of user.
Type of processing/purpose:
Collection of registration information/service administration data/service data re errors and interruptions – Legal basis: Performance of a function under legislation under the Broadcasting Act 2009 (as amended) which requires TG4 to establish and maintain a broadcasting service.
Type of processing/purpose:
Communications with commercial partners/direct marketing/promotional purposes – Legal Basis: consent.
What rights do you have in relation to your personal data under GDPR?
TG4 undertakes to respect the confidentiality of your personal data and ensure that you can exercise your rights.
You have the right to:
Request to know what personal data TG4 holds and the right to access your personal data.
Whenever it is technically possible, you can access your personal data directly within your account settings section. Until such time as this is technically possible, please contact us to assist you. You may make an access request, in writing, for a copy of your personal data held by TG4. TG4 may ask for further identification information from you before the information is released. TG4 has 30 days to comply with the access request, subject to the provisions of the Data Protection Acts.
Request correction of the personal data that we hold about you.
You have the right to have any incomplete or inaccurate information we hold about you corrected. Whenever it is technically possible, you can update your personal data directly within your account settings section.  Until such time as this is technically possible, please contact us to assist you. (s92 of the Data Protection Act 2018).
Object to processing of your personal data.
This right exists where we are relying on a legitimate interest as the legal basis for our processing and there is something about your particular situation, which makes you want to object to our processing of your personal data on this ground. You also have the right to object where we are processing your personal data for direct marketing purposes. At any point you may unsubscribe to the newsletter which at present is the only form of direct marketing carried out by TG4.  If in the future TG4 engages in additional direct marketing it will not contact users for direct marketing purposes unless the users have given consent and similarly it will not disclose this information to third parties for direct marketing purposes unless the users have given consent to TG4. Users may withdraw this consent at any time.
Request erasure of your personal data.
Whenever it is technically possible, you can erase your personal data directly within your account settings section.  Until such time as this is technically possible, please contact us to assist you. (s92 of the Data Protection Act 2018).
[
Request the transfer of your personal data.
We will provide to you, or to a third-party you have chosen, your personal data in a structured, commonly used, machine-readable format. Please note that this right only applies to automated information which you initially provided consent for us to use or where we used the information to perform a contract with you.
Withdraw your consent.
You have the right to withdraw your consent to us using your personal data. If you withdraw your consent, we may not be able to provide you with access to certain specific functionalities of the players.
Who do you contact in TG4 in relation to your  personal information held by TG4 collected through using the players?
Please email
dp@tg4.ie
Data Protection Commission
General information on data protection is available from the Data Protection Commission’s website (
www.dataprotection.ie
) and you may contact the Data Protection Commission if you believe TG4 is not complying with its data protection requirements. As an organisation which is required to register with the Office of the Data Protection Commissioner, more information on the type of information held by TG4 is available to view on the public register which is also on the Commissioner’s website.
Children’s Privacy
Some of our apps are designed for children under 13. We do not collect personally identifiable information from anyone under the age of 13. If you are a parent or guardian and you are aware that your child has provided us with personal data, please contact us. If we become aware that we have collected personal data from anyone under the age of 13 without verification of parental consent, we take steps to remove that information from our servers. We do however collect personal data from children under 13 who enter into competitions, but parental consent is required before children under 13 can enter into competitions.
Changes to this Privacy Statement
We may update our Privacy Statement from time to time to reflect any changes in technology, legislation or TG4 practices which may affect the way in which we process your personal information. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Statement on this page.
Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Statement, please email
dp@tg4.ie
or webmaster@tg4.ie